originalText.text: Came here because of a post I saw on IG. Atmosphere in the back was cute, with the balloons in the ceiling and the wall lighting. We came here for a birthday celebration and I must say the lay out is a little weird. The front was takeout and for that reason had me question what the dine in section would look like. Our server was nice who stated he was the assistant manager. Not sure if that was true because he wasn't well equipped to describe the items on the menu. The food was good, but not great. I liked the loaded lobster fries, the lobster Mac, (well seasoned) and the fried fish. The calamari was also good.  The drink I ordered was strong and for me the prices were reasonable as one plate can be shared in my opinion. They are a CASH only establishment. When I ask why they said because people are not honest and order a lot of food then call their card company and say it wasn't them. Also don't expect a quiet, classy dining experience.  This is not that kind of place. My drinks came in a plastic cup. Over all the visit wasn't bad. Just not my atmosphere.

originalText.text: One thing that I really liked was that the seating area gave me lounge vibes. I visited around 12:30 PM and it was pretty empty on a Saturday. I appreciated that because I really didn't wanna be around a crowd. We ordered so much food! My favorite was definitely the Rasta pasta. I would definitely recommend this because it was the right level of spicy and creamy. The portion size is huge so much that we ended up having to share it. The lobster mac & cheese and fried shrimp were also pretty good. For drinks, I would recommend the rum punch and the margarita. If you like a strong margarita on the rocks, this is the right choice for you. You can choose different flavors like passionfruit and mango. You can also request for the drinks to not be super strong and it'll still taste good. The music is on point and the waiters were attentive and helpful. Definitely a great seafood spot to check out for drinks, food and vibes. I want to go on a Friday night to see what the energy is like.

originalText.text:
I really enjoyed the ambiance of the restaurant. Super chill with great music and comfy seating. The waiters were laid bad but we tried to explain that we wanted to pay extra for the lobster mac cheese but ultimately we weren’t able to buy.

For our drinks we got a fruit punch and kiwi strawberry and looovveed them. I will warn you they are 32 oz so if you like sugary drinks you’re lucky to take them home. For food we shared calamari, and a fried shrimp, wings, garlic mash potatoes and mac and cheese combo. We weren’t a big fan of the calamari or the marinara sauce that came with it. Everything else was overall good. we couldn’t stop eating the garlic mash or mac and cheese. The fat fried shrimp with tartar sauce was a good combo. The fried chicken could have used some type of sauce and a little more seasoning. It was a little underwhelming. Otherwise I would comeback to try seething else.

originalText.text:
Surprisingly the food here is Amazing, and the layout was lovely and fun. The ballon’s on the ceiling and the wall signage were a nice touch. However the service was poor. Meals and drinks were mixed up or forgotten despite multiple asks and reminders, and the food took almost an hour to come out. Tasting the meals it was worth the wait though. The prices were a bit high and the drink menu limited. Reminiscent of a little dive bar. Also it’s worth it to point out they do not take credit cards; for those prices this breeds an air of sketchiness. Overall our little celebration turned out ok in the end and they did try and as stated the food was Amazing!
I think this place would do well with a bit of staff training and some touch up. Regardless I would definitely recommend this restaurant/lounge to anyone looking for a tasty bite to eat and I will definitely be returning.

originalText.text:
I was greeted at the entrance door by a club looking security guard at Lighthouse Fish Market on East 117th St. in Harlem.
I was quickly ask to go or dine in. As I said I will dine in I was guided towards the back of Lighthouse The gentleman also informed me the restaurant is cash only and pointed behind to the ATM machine. Information is so very important. As I walk to be seated I see the bar on the far back wall with 3 patrons sitting at the bar counter and watching the 3 big screen tv's above the bar back wall watching several NBA games having drinks and smoking hookah enjoying there evening. I was seated on the left was at a 4 person table in front of the bar right before the opened door way to another room which sounded like the party room with the music playing that sounded like a live DJ was in there and he was rocking. So this is a fact about myself I do not touch food with my hands. A project man since the 80's I am strictly knife & fork. So I did not order crab legs or any other seafood I would have to pickup. I went with the boneless flounder fried and laid to the side, sweet potatoes, macaroni salad. It was deeeeeeeelicious.
And I washed it down with a glass of fresh ice water. I was served and assisted by more than just my very pretty waitress. Here comes the stand out part of the evening for me I simply drank all the water in my glass. I asked pretty for a refill of my water she walk by the bar told my request to bartender and walked into the party room. I continued to enjoy my dinner and the bartender comes to my table when with a slim maybe 1 liter glass bottle of water and fills my glass of water and leaves the bottle on my table for the win.
Lighthouse Fish Market served me top to bottom I will definitely be going back in 2024.
